node.text:
I am honored fo be part of this documentary, made by the beautiful and talented @jeffwitzeman called “Beliefs & Stories, talking about the beliefs and stories we carry with us that impact us in profound and detrimental ways until we go through the process of awakening to know the truth of who we really are. ⁣
⁣
Featuring Jeff, @_al_boogie_ (Alec Zeck), @kellybroganmd, @dr.cassiehuckaby, @nakedtj_ , (Dr. Tommy John), @yojimd (Dr. Jo Yi), Dr. Christiane Northrup, Dr. Tom Cowan, fenixmeddr (Dr. Carrie Madej), and @xavier.dagba. ⁣
⁣
It is a beautiful portrait of the human spirit and the hurdles we can overcome to find our ultimate human condition—love. ⁣
⁣
It will be available on Vimeo on Demand this Friday, July 30tj.

Health Freedom for Humanity unites people from all walks of life under one common purpose: the reclamation and defense of health freedom. 

We are a community of advocates, parents, teachers, actors, veterans, doctors, lawyers, and friends, who stand to ensure Health Freedom for all people. We come from every religion, political affiliation, socioeconomic background, and philosophy on personal health, but are united in our belief that mandated medical procedures of any kind, medical coercion, or any restrictions on health choice violate basic human rights.

We welcome you to stand with us to protect and advance this right against all past, current, and future infringements, via education, personal empowerment, community support, and unity in action. 

We are Health Freedom for Humanity. 

Join us.

www.healthfreedomforhumanity.org

Oh you’re in deep. I get it. Many of us have been there, knee deep in the brutal abandonment of all logic simply because we wanted that dopamine hit that told us it’d all be ok….that things would get better. ⁣
⁣
We mistook the warning signs as invitations instead of red flags. ⁣
⁣
Intermittent reinforcement from your government: ⁣
⁣
You’re good. ⁣
⁣
Now you’re very bad and dirty, this is all your fault. ⁣
⁣
Now it’s not your fault—it’s their fault and they’re going to kill you. ⁣
⁣
Stay inside. ⁣
⁣
We’ll protect you. ⁣
⁣
Isn’t this always the game, the modus operandi of an abuser to drive their victim into the ground, then to demonstrate their GODness by picking them back up? Your neurochemistry becomes addicted to the highs… ⁣
⁣
And then the lows ⁣
⁣
Then the highs again. ⁣
⁣
You need a hit. ⁣
⁣
You need chaos, uncertainty and the ambiguity of someone you think you can trust but know deep down inside you can’t. ⁣
⁣
You watch them speak ill of others and yet, somehow believe they won’t do that to you because your heart aches so desperately for a savior. ⁣
⁣
And isn’t it always the path of the delusional to think that when you watch an abuser abuse others that you think you’re so special to them that they wouldn’t abuse you? ⁣
⁣
HOW YOU DO ONE THING ⁣
IS HOW YOU DO THEM ALL. ⁣
⁣
How you treat people, citizens and civilians in one country is how you think of and regard all people, citizens and civilians in other countries, including your own. ⁣
⁣
A human life is a human life. ⁣
⁣
Integrity is integrity. It’s not subjective to being molded to one’s desires and whims—it simply is. ⁣
⁣
Except when it’s in the way of a person or a government with an agenda, then integrity can be molded to the situation and the low hanging fruit, the most desperate and naive, are the first to be picked.⁣
⁣
They were just ripe for the soul harvest. ⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣

Part of leaving and exposing an abusiive relationship is learning to not care what people who are still inside the abusive and manipulative system or relationship think about you. They are still inside the system and are being manipulated just as you were when you were inside of it. ⁣
⁣
This is how these types of abusive and dysfunctional systems and relationships work on the personal and on the government level. ⁣
⁣
When you try to break free or expose the truth and warn others about the abusive behavior,  here comes the smear campaign: You will be called names, a liar, crazy, a troublemaker, a conspiracy theorist, or that you’re somehow only in it for the money when in actuality everyone is being lied to and abused—you’re just the only one aware of it yet OR you’re the only one willing to call it out. ⁣Your own children or family members may be left behind in the illusion and may even turn against you (my own children who I’m close with today didn’t speak to me for a while because they had been manipulated into believing I was a crazy and evil person when my marriage to an abusive person was ending). We were all being abused—I was the only one who could see it. 
⁣
If people still inside the delusion who believe they’re in a caring and reciprocal relationship aren’t willing to have conversations with you to know more about you or hear another side or hear another angle or point of view, if they’re easily triggered into calling you names, telling you you’re a bad person or acting like you’re crazy….⁣
⁣
Consider the source. ⁣
⁣
Go to logic, not emotions. ⁣
⁣
They are still inside of a relationship that is still abusing them and they are still dependent on them,  chances are just as you once were. And just as you couldn’t see it when you were inside of it, they can’t see it yet either. ⁣
⁣
They are still living in the illusion. 
⁣
Feel blessed that you are not and that you are out and that you see it. ⁣
⁣
All you can do is keep walking your truth, speaking in truth and staying in integrity. ⁣
⁣
These people will find out eventually what they’re dealing with and pray for them the damage is not deadly. ⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣

Sometimes I wish I had better memories or videos of the years I suffered in psychosis from the drugs I was put on and from the trauma and abuse I suffered in my marriage and relationships. ⁣
⁣
It seems like it was a different lifetime, maybe even a different world, it’s so far from who I am today and how I feel. ⁣
⁣
I do know I was full blown psychotic in many ways and for a long time, barely able to leave my home for years, shaking from akathasia and incapacitating anxiety, embarrassed, ashamed and nothing to be proud of. I believed my family and my marriage were collapsing because of me, not understanding the addictive nature of the trauma bond I had with my husband at the time. ⁣
⁣
My childhood wounds, never healed had collided with him who mirrored them for me, exposing what needed to be healed and the attachments I needed to break free from in order to shift from survival into creation. ⁣
⁣
I did same for him. ⁣
⁣
He gave me a box of darkness for years, but I held onto it, letting it singe my hands with the flames of infidelity, insecurity and projection to make me think everything was my fault. ⁣
⁣
The box he handed me was really a gift, ⁣
but I wasn’t ready to open it yet. ⁣
⁣
I needed to suffer more, ⁣
at my own hands, ⁣
not at anyone else’s. ⁣
⁣
I still feel a bit odd when I think of how incredibly dark those times were—it was a shit show of the highest order and to stand where I am today, I’m humbled, knowing many with a path like mine didn’t make it out alive, or maybe they’re alive but are still prisoners to the things, beliefs and people that oppress them. ⁣
⁣
That’s not living. That’s assisted suicide. ⁣
⁣
There was a time I felt I had nothing to show my children, I wasn’t a role model or a mother for them, but I know now in the deepest parts of myself I’ve shown them, more than anything the power of grit, perseverance and a belief in a higher power and purpose for our lives. ⁣
⁣
It’s the power of being on the path and in alignment with God, and these false systems and people keep trying to pull us off of our path. ⁣
⁣
I’m healed, and ready to tear some shit up and help these systems crumble, and I hope I inspire you to do the same. ⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣

When I was able to move myself out of victimhood my healing upleveled tenfold. ⁣
⁣
When I was able to see why those who had abused me did so, it took power away from them I’d been giving to them and shifted me into my own. ⁣
⁣
When I was able to hold space for others to have their own life experiences, even if I didn’t agree with them and even when those experiences were harmful to me, I was able to move into love with boundaries and it took me into the space of creation versus living in survival. ⁣
⁣
Learn to hold space for others who are still asleep. Learn to reach out in love and logic rather than being triggered, scared and reacting out of fear. Respect their process to awakening, even if it’s scary as hell to observe. ⁣
⁣
Is this scary? ⁣
⁣
Yes. ⁣
⁣
Have their bad decisions impacted you and us all in negative ways? ⁣
⁣
Yes. ⁣
⁣
But you don’t wake someone up by screaming at them or insulting them, you help wake them up by leading by example, staying calm, collected and in your integrity. ⁣
⁣
Their world is crumbling. ⁣
⁣
Let’s give them a safe haven, a lighthouse to come to.
